 Pre-Copa Sudamericana==\nFollowing the conclusion of the regular season, the teams placed 2nd to 5th qualify for the Liguilla in order to determine the \"Chile 2\" spot to the [[2016 Copa Sudamericana]]. However, teams that already played the [[2016 Copa Libertadores]] (from second stage onwards) and both finalists of [[2015 Copa Chile|Copa Chile]] are ineligible to compete in the Liguilla.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bases Campeonato Nacional - Primera Divisi\u00f3n Temporada 2015-2016 - Apertura y Clausura|language=Spanish|url=http://www.anfp.cl/documentos/1371251641-BASES%20PD%20Temporada%202015-2016.pdf|website=ANFP|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref> These teams are the following:\n* [[Colo-Colo]] (2nd), played in Copa Libertadores. Despite having qualified for Copa Sudamericana as being runners-up of Copa Chile, their spot was removed and given to a team in the aggregate table, as a team cannot qualify for two international tournaments in a calendar year.\n* [[Club Deportivo Palestino|Palestino]] (4th), already qualified for the Copa Sudamericana through the aggregate table.\n* [[C.D. Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n|Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n]] (5th), already qualified for the Copa Sudamericana through the aggregate table.\n\n{{4TeamBracket-2legs\n| RD1=Semifinals\n| RD2=Final\n\n| RD1-seed1=3\n| RD1-team1='''[[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]] \n| RD1-score1-1=3\n| RD1-score1-2=0\n| RD1-score1-A=3\n| RD1-seed2=8\n| RD1-team2=[[Deportes Iquique]]\n| RD1-score2-1=1\n| RD1-score2-2=1\n| RD1-score2-A=2\n\n| RD1-seed3=6\n| RD1-team3='''[[Santiago Wanderers]]\n| RD1-score3-1=0\n| RD1-score3-2=0\n| RD1-score3-A=0 (4)\n| RD1-seed4=7\n| RD1-team4=[[Deportes Antofagasta]]\n| RD1-score4-1=0\n| RD1-score4-2=0\n| RD1-score4-A=0 (3)\n\n| RD2-seed1=3\n| RD2-team1='''[[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]] \n| RD2-score1-1=0\n| RD2-score1-2=1\n| RD2-score1-A=1\n| RD2-seed2=6\n| RD2-team2=[[Santiago Wanderers]]\n| RD2-score2-1=0\n| RD2-score2-2=0\n| RD2-score2-A=0\n}}\n\n===Semifinals===\n{{Football 