 league topscorer   = [[Nicol\u00e1s Castillo]]<br /><small>(11 goals)\n| biggest home win   = [[Club Universidad de Chile|U. de Chile]] 8\u20131 [[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]]<br /><small>(24 January)</small>\n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n| highest attendance = 31,023 [[Club Universidad de Chile|U. de Chile]] 0\u20130 [[Colo-Colo]]<br /><small>(20 March)</small>\n| attendance         = 622,725\n| average attendance = 5,189\n| matches            = 120\n| total goals        = 356\n| prevseason = [[2015 Torneo Apertura (Chile)|2015\u2013A]]\n| nextseason = [[2016 Torneo Apertura (Chile)|2016\u2013A]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2016 Campeonato Nacional Clausura Scotiabank'''  was the 98th [[Chilean Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Chilean League top flight]], in which [[Club Deportivo Universidad Cat\u00f3lica|Universidad Cat\u00f3lica]] won its 11st league title.\n\n==Standings==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=UC |name_UC =[[Club Deportivo Universidad Cat\u00f3lica|Universidad Cat\u00f3lica]]\n|team2=CC |name_CC =[[Colo-Colo]]\n|team3=OHI|name_OHI=[[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]]\n|team4=PAL|name_PAL=[[C.D. Palestino|Palestino]]\n|team5=UDC|name_UDC=[[C.D. Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n|Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n]]\n|team6=SW |name_SW =[[Santiago Wanderers]]\n|team7=ANT|name_ANT=[[Deportes Antofagasta]]\n|team8=DIQ|name_DIQ=[[Deportes Iquique]]\n|team9=HUA|name_HUA=[[Huachipato]]\n|team10=UCH|name_UCH=[[Club Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]]\n|team11=SL |name_SL =[[San Luis de Quillota]]\n|team12=AUD|name_AUD=[[Audax Italiano]]\n|team13=UE |name_UE =[[Uni\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]]\n|team14=COB|name_COB=[[Cobresal]]\n|team15=SMA|name_SMA=[[San Marcos de Arica]]\n|team16=ULC|name_ULC=[[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]]\n|win_UC =9|draw_UC =2|loss_UC =4|gf_UC =33|ga_UC =25\n|win_CC =8|draw_CC =4|loss_CC =3|gf_CC =19|ga_CC =11\n|win_OHI=8|draw_OHI=4|loss_OHI=3|gf_OHI=28|ga_OHI=24\n|win_PAL=6|draw_PAL=7|loss_PAL=2|gf_PAL=24|ga_PAL=18\n|win_UDC=8|draw_UDC=1|loss_UDC=6|gf_UDC=22|ga_UDC=24\n|win_SW =6|draw_SW =5|loss_SW =4|gf_SW =31|ga_SW =26\n|win_ANT=6|draw_ANT=3|loss_ANT=6|gf_ANT=23|ga_ANT=18\n|win_DIQ=4|draw_DIQ=7|loss_DIQ=4|gf_DIQ=22|ga_DIQ=21\n|win_HUA=4|draw_HUA=7|loss_HUA=4|gf_HUA=26|ga_HUA=27\n|win_UCH=3|draw_UCH=7|loss_UCH=5|gf_UCH=29|ga_UCH=25\n|win_SL =3|draw_SL =7|loss_SL =5|gf_SL =22|ga_SL =25\n|win_AUD=3|draw_AUD=7|loss_AUD=5|gf_AUD=16|ga_AUD=19\n|win_UE =2|draw_UE =9|loss_UE =4|gf_UE =20|ga_UE =24\n|win_COB=3|draw_COB=5|loss_COB=7|gf_COB=14|ga_COB=21\n|win_SMA=2|draw_SMA=6|loss_SMA=7|gf_SMA=10|ga_SMA=17\n|win_ULC=2|draw_ULC=5|loss_ULC=8|gf_ULC=16|ga_ULC=30\n\n|col_CLGS=gold|text_CLGS=Champions and [[2017 Copa Libertadores|2017 Copa Libertadores group stage]]\n|result1=CLGS\n|col_CL=#FFFFCC|text_CL=[[#Liguilla Pre-Copa Sudamericana|Liguilla Pre-Sudamericana]]\n|result3=CL|result6=CL|result7=CL|result8=CL\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|update=30 April 2016 \n|source=[https://int.soccerway.com/national/chile/primera-division/20152016/clausura/r31527/tables/ Standings]\n}}\n\n==Liguilla Pre-Copa Sudamericana==\nFollowing the conclusion of the regular season, the teams placed 2nd to 5th qualify for the Liguilla in order to determine the \"Chile 2\" spot to the [[2016 Copa Sudamericana]]. However, teams that already played the [[2016 Copa Libertadores]] (from second stage onwards) and both finalists of [[2015 Copa Chile|Copa Chile]] are ineligible to compete in the Liguilla.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bases Campeonato Nacional - Primera Divisi\u00f3n Temporada 2015-2016 - Apertura y Clausura|language=Spanish|url=http://www.anfp.cl/documentos/1371251641-BASES%20PD%20Temporada%202015-2016.pdf|website=ANFP|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref> These teams are the following:\n* [[Colo-Colo]] (2nd), played in Copa Libertadores. Despite having qualified for Copa Sudamericana as being runners-up of Copa Chile, their spot was removed and given to a team in the aggregate table, as a team cannot qualify for two international tournaments in a calendar year.\n* [[Club Deportivo Palestino|Palestino]] (4th), already qualified for the Copa Sudamericana through the aggregate table.\n* [[C.D. Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n|Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n]] (5th), already qualified for the Copa Sudamericana through the aggregate table.\n\n{{4TeamBracket-2legs\n| RD1=Semifinals\n| RD2=Final\n\n| RD1-seed1=3\n| RD1-team1='''[[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]] \n| RD1-score1-1=3\n| RD1-score1-2=0\n| RD1-score1-A=3\n| RD1-seed2=8\n| RD1-team2=[[Deportes Iquique]]\n| RD1-score2-1=1\n| RD1-score2-2=1\n| RD1-score2-A=2\n\n| RD1-seed3=6\n| RD1-team3='''[[Santiago Wanderers]]\n| RD1-score3-1=0\n| RD1-score3-2=0\n| RD1-score3-A=0 (4)\n| RD1-seed4=7\n| RD1-team4=[[Deportes Antofagasta]]\n| RD1-score4-1=0\n| RD1-score4-2=0\n| RD1-score4-A=0 (3)\n\n| RD2-seed1=3\n| RD2-team1='''[[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]] \n| RD2-score1-1=0\n| RD2-score1-2=1\n| RD2-score1-A=1\n| RD2-seed2=6\n| RD2-team2=[[Santiago Wanderers]]\n| RD2-score2-1=0\n| RD2-score2-2=0\n| RD2-score2-A=0\n}}\n\n===Semifinals===\n{{Football box collapsible\n|date         = {{Start date|2016|05|04|df=y}}\n|time         = 22:00\n|round        = 1st Leg\n|team1        = [[Deportes Iquique]]\n|score        = 1\u20133\n|report       = [http://www.anfp.cl/noticia/26248/ohiggins-se-recupero-y-toma-la-delantera-en-la-llave-frente-a-deportes-iquique Report]\n|team2        = [[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]]\n|goals1       = [[Mauricio Zenteno|Zenteno]] {{sent off|0|51}}<br>[[Manuel Villalobos|Villalobos]] {{goal|70}}\n|goals2       = [[Basti\u00e1n San Juan|San Juan]] {{goal|17}}<br>[[Albert Acevedo|Acevedo]] {{goal|38}}<br>[[Cristian Insaurralde|Insaurralde]] {{goal|49}}\n|stadium      = [[Estadio Tierra de Campeones]], [[Iquique]]\n|attendance   = 3,180\n|referee      = Carlos Ulloa\n}}\n\n{{Football box collapsible\n|date         = {{Start date|2016|05|08|df=y}}\n|time         = 18:00\n|round        = 2nd Leg\n|team1    